# Review And Profile

Use review/profile commands to inspect feedback loops and project-level understanding.

## `skills-seed review import`

Purpose:

- Import local code review comments from JSON.
- Preserve review feedback so it can be compared with learned pattern coverage.

Flag:

- `--from-file`: path to the JSON file containing review comments.

Use case:

- `skills-seed review import --from-file review-comments.json`

## `skills-seed review stats`

Purpose:

- Show how imported review comments relate to pattern hits.
- Measure whether existing patterns would have prevented reviewed issues.

Flag:

- `--line-window`: line distance allowed when matching review comments with pattern hits.

Use cases:

- `skills-seed review stats`
- `skills-seed review stats --line-window 5`

## `skills-seed profile show`

Purpose:

- Display the current project profile summary.
- Inspect whether skills-seed understands project architecture, language, modules, utilities, and validation commands correctly.

Use case:

- `skills-seed profile show`

## `skills-seed profile refresh`

Purpose:

- Re-analyze and save the project profile using AI.

Flag:

- `--language, -l`: override detected language.

Use when:

- Architecture changed.
- Major module boundaries changed.
- The generated Skill routes tasks poorly.
- Validation commands or profile facts are stale.

After refreshing the profile, run `skills-seed generate skills` or `skills-seed sync`.
